  "text": "The k-server problem, defined by Manasse, McGeoch, and Sleator [CITATION_1] , consists of an n-point metric space, and k mobile servers (k < n) residing in points of this metric space. A sequence of requests is presented, each request is associated with a point in the metric space and must be served by moving one of the k servers to the request point. The cost of an algorithm for serving a sequence of requests is the total distance traveled by the servers.",
